comment.author: 23103743@N05
comment._content: Perhaps the woman who was later Assistant Director of the U.S. Mint, but started as secretary/assistant to the director. Evening public ledger., October 31, 1922, Night Extra, Page 22 chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045211/1922-10-31/ed-... has a piece on her, with a picture that could be a match.

comment.author: 23103743@N05
comment._content: NYT of October 30, 1938 select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F10F15F63B581A7A... announces her retirement from the U.S. Treasury at the age of 73, after 33 years of service, including a presidential exemption from the compulsory retirement age of 70.
